\[\textbf{X}_{c_{\!\text{in}},i_{1},i_{2}}=\sum_{c_{\!\text{out}}=1}^{C_{\! \text{out}}}\sum_{k_{1}=1}^{K_{1}}\sum_{k_{2}=1}^{K_{2}}\sum_{o_{1}=1}^{O_{1} }\sum_{o_{2}=1}^{O_{2}}\mathbf{\Pi}^{(1)}_{i_{1},o_{1},k_{1}}\mathbf{\Pi}^{(2)}_{i_{2 },o_{2},k_{2}}\,\mathbf{Y}_{c_{\!\text{out}},k_{1},k_{2}}\tilde{\textbf{W}}_{c_{ \!\text{out}},c_{\!\text{in}},k_{1},k_{2}} \tag{11}\]

Our goal is to turn the express the above as matrix multiplication. To do that, we first define the matrix reshape \(\mathbf{X}\) of **X** via \(\mathbf{X}\in\mathbb{R}^{C_{\!\text{in}}\times I_{1}I_{2}}\) such that \([\mathbf{X}]_{c_{\!\text{in}},(i_{1},i_{2})}=\textbf{X}_{c_{\!\text{in}},i_{1},i_ {2}}\). Next, we consider a transposed kernel **W** of \(\tilde{\textbf{W}}\) with changed order of the first two indices, i.e.\(\textbf{W}\in\mathbb{R}^{C_{\!\text{in}}\times C_{\!\text{out}}\times K_{1}\times K _{2}}\) such that

\[\textbf{W}_{c_{\!\text{in}},c_{\!\text{out}},k_{1},k_{2}}=\tilde{\textbf{W}}_{ c_{\!\text{out}},c_{\!\text{in}},k_{1},k_{2}}\,. \tag{12}\]

This transposition is necessary to convert the kernel's layout in the ML framework to a layout that admits Equation (11) to be expressed as matrix multiplication. Using a matrix reshape \(\mathbf{W}\) of **W** via \(\mathbf{W}\in\mathbb{R}^{C_{\!\text{in}}\times C_{\!\text{out}}K_{1}K_{2}}\) such that \([\mathbf{W}]_{c_{\!\text{in}},(c_{\!\text{out}},k_{1},k_{2})}=\textbf{W}_{c_{\! \text{in}},c_{\!\text{out}},k_{1},k_{2}}\), we can express Equation (11) as matrix multiplication

\[\mathbf{X}=\mathbf{W}[\![\textbf{Y}]\!]_{\text{T}} \tag{13}\]

